---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Shingai Thornton and Halcyonic Systems">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="ab-title">About</h1>

    <div class="ab-intro">
      <div class="ab-kingfisher">
        <img src="/logo.png" alt="Halcyonic kingfisher" class="ab-bird" />
      </div>
      <div class="ab-story">
        <p>
          The halcyon is the kingfisher of Greek myth — the bird that nests on calm seas.
          Ancient sailors believed it could still the waves during its brooding days, creating
          a window of peace in the middle of winter storms. That stillness is what we pursue:
          a point of formal rigor in the chaos of transdisciplinary complexity.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ab-bio">
      <p>
        I'm Shingai Thornton. I defended my M.S. thesis in Systems Science at Binghamton University
        in April 2026 — passed with no revisions. My committee: Cliff Joslyn (PNNL, categorical systems science
        and hypergraph theory), Sadamori Kojaku (network science, stochastic block models),
        and Carlos Gershenson (complexity science, self-organization).
      </p>
      <p>
        Before that, I spent a decade researching blockchains, cryptoeconomics, and political economy.
        Halcyonic Systems is where this work comes together — formal systems science applied to
        governance, cryptoeconomics, and brain-inspired computing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ab-lineage">
      <h2 class="ab-section-header">Intellectual Lineage</h2>
      <p>
        Bertalanffy's General System Theory established the field. Mobus formalized it into a
        rigorous ontology with the 8-tuple system definition. The category theory thread —
        particularly Joslyn's work on hypergraph-based categorical systems — provides the
        mathematical foundation. The Common Core Theorem (K &cong; <strong>2</strong>) shows
        that seven independent traditions of system definition share a single categorical structure:
        a system is a morphism f : R &rarr; T.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ab-body-of-work">
      <h2 class="ab-section-header">The Body of Work</h2>
      <p>
        Four projects span four modes of systems science work: BERT (framework and computational tool),
        the U.S. Trade Network thesis (quantitative empirical research), Facets (interactive epistemological
        classification), and the Bitcoin Deep Systems Analysis (theoretical domain application). Together
        they form a coherent research program — not a random collection.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ab-connect">
      <h2 class="ab-section-header">Connect</h2>
      <div class="ab-links">
        <a href="mailto:shingai@halcyonic.systems" class="ab-link">
          shingai@halcyonic.systems <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/halcyonic-systems" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ab-link">
          GitHub <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://halcyonic.discourse.group" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ab-link">
          Forums <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://ideas.halcyonic.systems" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ab-link">
          Substack <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ab-title {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-frost-slate);
  }

  .ab-intro {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .ab-kingfisher {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ab-bird {
    width: 140px;
    height: 140px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .ab-story {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .ab-story p {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-frost-slate-dim);
  }

  .ab-bio {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .ab-bio p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-frost-slate-dim);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .ab-section-header {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-frost-teal-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ab-lineage, .ab-body-of-work {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-frost-border);
  }

  .ab-lineage p, .ab-body-of-work p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-frost-slate-dim);
  }

  .ab-connect {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-frost-border);
  }

  .ab-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .ab-link {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-frost-teal);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .ab-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .ab-intro {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>
